			Node:
			(type) h1
			(layer)1
				Element:h1
				Element:a
					Event Types & Payloads
				Element:span
			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
				Element:p
					Each event has a similar JSON schema, but a unique
				Element:code
					payload
					object that is determined by its event type.
			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
				Element:p
					Event names are used by
				Element:a
					repository webhooks
					to specify which events the webhook should receive. The included payloads below are from webhook deliveries but match events returned by the
				Element:a
					Events API
					(except where noted). The Events API uses the CamelCased name (e.g.
				Element:code
					CommitCommentEvent
					) in the
				Element:code
					type
					field of an event object and does not include the
				Element:code
					repository
					or
				Element:code
					sender
					fields in the event payload object.
			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
				Element:p
				Element:strong
					Note:
					Some of these events may not be rendered in timelines, they're only created for various internal and webhook purposes.

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								CreateEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Represents a created repository, branch, or tag.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Note: webhooks will not receive this event for created repositories. Additionally, webhooks will not receive this event for tags if more than three tags are pushed at once.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											ref_type
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The object that was created. Can be one of "repository", "branch", or "tag"
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											ref
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The git ref (or
										Element:code
											null
											if only a repository was created).
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											master_branch
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The name of the repository's default branch (usually
										Element:code
											master
											).
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											description
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The repository's current description.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:

							Element:h2
							Element:a
								ForkApplyEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a patch is applied in the Fork Queue.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are
							Element:strong
								no longer created
								, but it's possible that they exist in timelines of some users.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:

										Element:code
											after
										Element:td

							Element:h2
							Element:a
								IssueCommentEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when an
							Element:a
								issue comment
								is created, edited, or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed on the comment. Can be one of "created", "edited", or "deleted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the comment if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[body][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the body if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											issue
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											issue
											the comment belongs to.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											comment
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											comment
											itself.

			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								IssuesEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when an
							Element:a
								issue
								is assigned, unassigned, labeled, unlabeled, opened, edited, milestoned, demilestoned, closed, or reopened.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Can be one of "assigned", "unassigned", "labeled", "unlabeled", "opened", "edited", "milestoned", "demilestoned", "closed", or "reopened".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											issue
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											issue
											itself.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the issue if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[title][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the title if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[body][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the body if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											assignee
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The optional user who was assigned or unassigned from the issue.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											label
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The optional label that was added or removed from the issue.
						Node:

						(layer)2
									Node:

								deleted

						Node:

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								MemberEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a user is added or removed as a collaborator to a repository, or has their permissions changed .
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											member
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											user
											that was added.

								MilestoneEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a milestone is created, closed, opened, edited, or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger hooks.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c

											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3

										Element:th

										Element:tr

										Element:code
											action

										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Can be one of
										Element:code

										Element:code
											"closed"

										Element:code
											"opened"

											changes

											The previous version of the description if the action was

			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								OrganizationEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a user is added, removed, or invited to an Organization.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger organization hooks.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Can be one of
										Element:code
											"member_added"
											,
										Element:code
											"member_removed"
											, or
										Element:code
											"member_invited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											invitation
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The invitation for the user or email if the action is
										Element:code
											"member_invited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											membership
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The membership between the user and the organization. Not present when the action is
										Element:code
											"member_invited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											organization
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The organization in question.
						Node:

						(layer)2

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								PageBuildEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Represents an attempted build of a GitHub Pages site, whether successful or not.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered on push to a GitHub Pages enabled branch (
							Element:code
								gh-pages
								for project pages,
							Element:code
								master
								for user and organization pages).
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger hooks.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload

										Element:tr

											build
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td

										Element:a

											itself.

			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								ProjectCardEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a
							Element:a
								project card
								is created, updated, moved, converted to an issue, or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action performed on the project card. Can be "created", "edited", "converted", "moved", or "deleted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the project card if the action was "edited" or "converted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[note][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the note if the action was "edited" or "converted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											after_id
										Element:td
										Element:code
											integer
										Element:td
											The id of the card that this card now follows if the action was "moved". Will be
										Element:code
											null
											if it is the first card in a column.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											project_card
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											project card
											itself.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2

			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								ProjectColumnEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a
							Element:a
								project column
								is created, updated, moved, or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed on the project column. Can be one of "created", "edited", "moved" or "deleted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the project column if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[name][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the name if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											after_id
										Element:td
										Element:code
											integer
										Element:td
											The id of the column that this column now follows if the action was "moved". Will be
										Element:code
											null
											if it is the first column in a project.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											project_column
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											project column
											itself.

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								ProjectEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a
							Element:a
								project
								is created, updated, closed, reopened, or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed on the project. Can be one of "created", "edited", "closed", "reopened", or "deleted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object

										Element:span
			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								PullRequestEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a
							Element:a
								pull request
								is assigned, unassigned, labeled, unlabeled, opened, edited, closed, reopened, or synchronized. Also triggered when a pull request review is requested, or when a review request is removed.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Can be one of "assigned", "unassigned", "review_requested", "review_request_removed", "labeled", "unlabeled", "opened", "edited", "closed", or "reopened". If the action is "closed" and the
										Element:code
											merged
											key is
										Element:code
											false
											, the pull request was closed with unmerged commits. If the action is "closed" and the
										Element:code
											merged
											key is
										Element:code
											true
											, the pull request was merged. While webhooks are also triggered when a pull request is synchronized, Events API timelines don't include pull request events with the "synchronize" action.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											number
										Element:td
										Element:code
											integer
										Element:td
											The pull request number.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the comment if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[title][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the title if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[body][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the body if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											pull_request
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											pull request
											itself.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Webhook event name
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:p
										Element:code
											pull_request
						Node:

						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								PullRequestReviewCommentEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a
							Element:a
								comment on a pull request's unified diff
								is created, edited, or deleted (in the Files Changed tab).
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed on the comment. Can be one of "created", "edited", or "deleted".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the comment if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[body][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the body if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											pull_request
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td

										Element:a
											pull request
											the comment belongs to.

										Element:td
										Element:code

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								PushEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a repository branch is pushed to. In addition to branch pushes, webhook
							Element:a
								are also triggered when repository tags are pushed.
							Element:code
								push
								events
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								The Events API
							Element:code
								PushEvent
								payload is described in the table below. The example payload below that is from a webhook delivery and will differ from the Events API
							Element:code
								PushEvent
								payload.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											ref
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The full Git ref that was pushed. Example:
										Element:code
											"refs/heads/master"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											head
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The SHA of the most recent commit on
										Element:code
											ref
											after the push.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											before
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The SHA of the most recent commit on
										Element:code
											ref
											before the push.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											size
										Element:td
										Element:code
											integer
										Element:td
											The number of commits in the push.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											distinct_size
										Element:td
										Element:code
											integer
										Element:td
											The number of distinct commits in the push.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits
										Element:td
										Element:code
											array
										Element:td
											An array of commit objects describing the pushed commits. (The array includes a maximum of 20 commits. If necessary, you can use the
										Element:a
											Commits API
											to fetch additional commits. This limit is applied to timeline events only and isn't applied to webhook deliveries.)
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][sha]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The SHA of the commit.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][message]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The commit message.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][author]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The git author of the commit.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][author][name]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The git author's name.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][author][email]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The git author's email address.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][url]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											url
										Element:td
											Points to the commit API resource.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											commits[][distinct]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											boolean
										Element:td
											Whether this commit is distinct from any that have been pushed before.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Webhook event name
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:p
										Element:code
											push

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								RepositoryEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when a repository is created, made public, or made private.
							Element:a
								Organization hooks
								are also triggered when a repository is deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger hooks.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. This can be one of "created", "deleted" (
										Element:a
											organization hooks
											only), "publicized", or "privatized".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											repository
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The
										Element:a
											repository
											itself.

								StatusEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when the status of a Git commit changes.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger hooks.
						Node:

											The new state. Can be

										Element:code

											The optional human-readable description added to the status.

										Element:code
											target_url
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string

											The optional link added to the status.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											branches
										Element:td
										Element:code
											array
										Element:td
											An array of branch objects containing the status' SHA. Each branch contains the given SHA, but the SHA may or may not be the head of the branch. The array includes a maximum of 10 branches.

			Node:
			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								TeamEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Triggered when an organization's team is created or deleted.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								Events of this type are not visible in timelines. These events are only used to trigger organization hooks.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Can be one of
										Element:code
											"created"
											,
										Element:code
											"deleted"
											,
										Element:code
											"edited"
											,
										Element:code
											"added_to_repository"
											, or
										Element:code
											"removed_from_repository"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											team
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The team itself.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The changes to the team if the action was "edited".
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[description][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the description if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[name][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the name if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[privacy][from]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The previous version of the team's privacy if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[repository][permissions][from][admin]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											boolean
										Element:td
											The previous version of the team member's
										Element:code
											admin
											permission on a repository, if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[repository][permissions][from][pull]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											boolean
										Element:td
											The previous version of the team member's
										Element:code
											pull
											permission on a repository, if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											changes[repository][permissions][from][push]
										Element:td
										Element:code
											boolean
										Element:td
											The previous version of the team member's
										Element:code
											push
											permission on a repository, if the action was
										Element:code
											"edited"
											.
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											repository
										Element:td
										Element:code
											object
										Element:td
											The repository that was added or removed from to the team's purview if the action was
										Element:code
											"added_to_repository"
											,
										Element:code
											"removed_from_repository"
											, or
										Element:code
											"edited"
											. For
										Element:code
											"edited"
											actions,
										Element:code
											repository
											also contains the team's new permission levels for the repository.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Webhook event name
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:p
										Element:code
											team
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Webhook payload example
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:pre
										Element:code
										Element:span
											{
										Element:span
										Element:span
											"action"
										Element:span
											:
										Element:span
											"created"
										Element:span
											,
										Element:span
										Element:span
											"team"
										Element:span
											:{
										Element:span
										Element:span
											"name"
										Element:span
											:
										Element:span
											"team baxter"
										Element:span
											,
										Element:span
										Element:span
											"id"
										Element:span
											:
										Element:span
											2175394
										Element:span
											,
										Element:span
										Element:span
											"slug"
										Element:span
											:
										Element:span

			(type) c
			(layer)1
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:h2
							Element:a
								WatchEvent
							Element:span
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								The WatchEvent is related to
							Element:a
								starring a repository
								, not
							Element:a
								watching
								. See
							Element:a
								this API blog post
								for an explanation.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
							Element:p
								The events actor is the
							Element:a
								user
								who starred a repository, and the events repository is the
							Element:a
								repository
								that was starred.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:h3
										Element:a
											Events API payload
										Element:span
									Node:
									(type) c
									(layer)3
										Element:table
										Element:thead
										Element:tr
										Element:th
											Key
										Element:th
											Type
										Element:th
											Description
										Element:tbody
										Element:tr
										Element:td
										Element:code
											action
										Element:td
										Element:code
											string
										Element:td
											The action that was performed. Currently, can only be
										Element:code
											started
											.
						Node:
						(type) c
						(layer)2
									Node:
									(type) c

									Node:
